    <div>
      <div class="section-label">05 · Risk Register</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">What Could Go Wrong &amp;<br>How We Mitigate It</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Scored by Probability × Impact (1–5 each). Anything above 12 is tracked weekly.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="risk-row fade-in">
    <div class="risk-score rs-high">16</div>
    <div>
      <div class="risk-title">THIN SUPPLY — Not enough suppliers to deliver 3+ bids per RFQ</div>
      <div class="risk-body">The core product promise breaks if contractors post and get 1–2 bids. Suppliers are inherently harder to acquire than contractors. P=4, I=4.</div>
      <div class="risk-mitigation">→ Mitigation: Off-platform Google Maps outreach is the primary counter. Pre-seed 50+ suppliers in RI before first contractor onboards. Track avg bids/RFQ daily. Halt contractor expansion if it drops below 2.5.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="risk-row fade-in">
    <div class="risk-score rs-high">15</div>
    <div>
      <div class="risk-title">TCPA VIOLATION — AI calling triggers regulatory action</div>
      <div class="risk-body">TCPA fines are $500–$1,500 per call per violation. A class action from even 100 suppliers = $50K–$150K exposure. P=3, I=5.</div>
      <div class="risk-mitigation">→ Mitigation: Press-1 opt-in architecture (never outbound without consent signal). Max 1 call/supplier/day. Full call log retained. Legal review of call scripts before launch. Opt-out list enforced at DB level, not app level.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="risk-row fade-in">
    <div class="risk-score rs-high">12</div>
    <div>
      <div class="risk-title">SEO DISRUPTION — Google algorithm change de-ranks supplier pages</div>
      <div class="risk-body">If Google classifies auto-generated supplier pages as thin content, organic traffic collapses. P=3, I=4.</div>
      <div class="risk-mitigation">→ Mitigation: Enrich pages with real transaction data (prices, reviews, response rates) ASAP. Claimed pages get supplier-added content. Diversify traffic via autoblog, Reddit/social listening, and paid to reduce SEO dependency below 40%.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="risk-row fade-in">
    <div class="risk-score rs-med">9</div>
    <div>
      <div class="risk-title">PROCORE ENTRY — Procore launches competitive procurement feature</div>
      <div class="risk-body">Procore has $1B+ ARR and deep contractor relationships. If they launch a procurement module with off-platform outreach, they can out-distribute us. P=2, I=4 (they move slowly).</div>
      <div class="risk-mitigation">→ Mitigation: 18-month window before they could ship anything comparable. Win enough contractors and suppliers fast enough that switching cost is real. AI negotiation + split-bid are hard to replicate. Focus on SMB contractors Procore ignores.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="risk-row fade-in">
    <div class="risk-score rs-med">8</div>
    <div>
      <div class="risk-title">AI HALLUCINATION — Voice RFQ misinterprets material specs</div>
      <div class="risk-body">Contractor says "I need 2x4s" and AI structures it as 2×4×8 when they meant 2×4×12. Wrong material ordered. P=4, I=2.</div>
      <div class="risk-mitigation">→ Mitigation: Mandatory confirmation screen shows AI-parsed RFQ before submission. Contractor must explicitly approve each line item. Dispute resolution flow for wrong-spec deliveries. Supplier and contractor both confirm specs at deal closure.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="risk-row fade-in">
    <div class="risk-score rs-low">4</div>
    <div>
      <div class="risk-title">PAYMENT FRAUD — Escrow funds misdirected in Phase 3</div>
      <div class="risk-body">Payment fraud via fake supplier accounts. Low probability with Stripe KYC but non-zero. P=1, I=4.</div>
      <div class="risk-mitigation">→ Mitigation: Stripe Connect with full KYC before any supplier can receive payouts. Payments held in escrow until delivery confirmed. Contractor confirms receipt before funds release. Max payout delay of 7 days for new suppliers.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

